content.text:
# Fix: Top-Level Await Build Failure in main.js

## Priority: HIGH â€” Frontend cannot build (`npm run build` fails)

## Files to modify
- `frontend/src/main.js`

## Problem

`frontend/src/main.js` line 15 uses a bare `await` at the module top level. Vite's esbuild transpiler rejects this for the default browser targets, causing `npm run build` to fail with `Transform failed with 1 error`.

## Instructions

Replace the entire content of `frontend/src/main.js` with:

```javascript
import { createApp } from 'vue';
import App from './App.vue';
import router from './router';
import { createPinia } from 'pinia';
import { useAuthStore } from './stores/auth';

import 'element-plus/dist/index.css';
import './styles/main.css';

const app = createApp(App);
const pinia = createPinia();
app.use(pinia);

const authStore = useAuthStore();
authStore.restoreSession().then(() => {
  app.use(router);
  app.mount('#app');
});
```

## Verification

Run from `frontend/`: `npm run build`

The build should complete without the `Transform failed` error.

