# Fix: Audit Trail Silently Swallows Failures

## Priority: HIGH â€” Undermines "immutable audit trail" requirement

## Files to modify
- `backend/src/main/java/com/shiftworks/jobops/service/AuditService.java`

## Problem

`AuditService.log()` wraps the entire audit write in a try/catch that only logs the error and returns. Audit entries can be silently lost. The prompt requires "immutable audit trails" â€” silently dropping entries is a compliance liability.

## Instructions

Open `backend/src/main/java/com/shiftworks/jobops/service/AuditService.java`.

Replace the entire `log()` method (lines 26-43):

```java
    public void log(Long userId, String action, String entityType, Long entityId, Object beforeValue, Object afterValue) {
        try {
            AuditLog entry = new AuditLog();
            if (userId != null) {
                userRepository.findById(userId).ifPresent(entry::setUser);
            }
            entry.setAction(action);
            entry.setEntityType(entityType);
            entry.setEntityId(entityId);
            entry.setBeforeValue(toJson(beforeValue));
            entry.setAfterValue(toJson(afterValue));
            entry.setIpAddress(resolveIp());
            entry.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());
            auditLogRepository.save(entry);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            log.error("Failed to write audit log: action={}, entity={}/{}", action, entityType, entityId, e);
        }
    }
```

With:

```java
    @org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional(propagation = org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void log(Long userId, String action, String entityType, Long entityId, Object beforeValue, Object afterValue) {
        try {
            AuditLog entry = new AuditLog();
            if (userId != null) {
                userRepository.findById(userId).ifPresent(entry::setUser);
            }
            entry.setAction(action);
            entry.setEntityType(entityType);
            entry.setEntityId(entityId);
            entry.setBeforeValue(toJson(beforeValue));
            entry.setAfterValue(toJson(afterValue));
            entry.setIpAddress(resolveIp());
            entry.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());
            auditLogRepository.save(entry);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            log.error("CRITICAL: Failed to write audit log: action={}, entity={}/{}", action, entityType, entityId, e);
            throw new RuntimeException("Audit trail write failed â€” refusing to proceed without audit record", e);
        }
    }
```

Key changes:
1. Added `@Transactional(propagation = REQUIRES_NEW)` so audit runs in its own transaction (won't roll back the caller's transaction on success, and audit failures won't silently pass)
2. The catch block now re-throws as `RuntimeException` so callers know the audit failed
3. Log message prefixed with `CRITICAL` for easier alerting

## Verification

`cd backend && mvn compile -q` â€” confirm compilation.

