content.text:
# Fix: Admin Dashboard Claim Success Rate Chart Is a Flat-Line Stub

## Priority: LOW â€” Dashboard shows misleading trend data

## Files to modify
- `frontend/src/views/AdminDashboardView.vue`

## Problem

The `claimTrend` computed property repeats the current `claimSuccess.value.rate` for every day in the date range, producing a flat horizontal line instead of real time-series data.

## Instructions

Open `frontend/src/views/AdminDashboardView.vue`.

Find the `claimTrend` computed property (around line 163):

```javascript
const claimTrend = computed(() => {
  const [start, end] = dateRange.value;
  const days = dayjs(end).diff(dayjs(start), 'day') + 1;
  const points = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < days; i += 1) {
    points.push({
      date: dayjs(start).add(i, 'day').format('YYYY-MM-DD'),
      rate: claimSuccess.value.rate || 0
    });
